('chunk_ea491bcde0511b61c5','file_1dcbc968a2bb8c1157','visual-art.md','1. Subject Overview','Visual Art at IISH belongs to the **MYP Arts** subject group. In the Arts, students act as both **artist** and **critic** — they investigate the world of art, develop and refine their own ideas and skills, create original artwork, and evaluate their process and product. Learning is driven by **inquiry**, structured around **key and related concepts**, set in **global contexts**, and assessed against **four criteria**.','{"subject":2,"overview":1,"visual":1,"art":2,"iish":1,"belongs":1,"the":3,"myp":1,"arts":2,"group":1,"students":1,"act":1,"both":1,"artist":1,"and":7,"critic":1,"they":1,"investigate":1,"world":1,"develop":1,"refine":1,"their":2,"own":1,"ideas":1,"skills":1,"create":1,"original":1,"artwork":1,"evaluate":1,"process":1,"product":1,"learning":1,"driven":1,"inquiry":1,"structured":1,"around":1,"key":1,"related":1,"concepts":1,"set":1,"global":1,"contexts":1,"assessed":1,"against":1,"four":1,"criteria":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_08d9b078c92da3e307','file_1dcbc968a2bb8c1157','visual-art.md','The Four MYP Arts Criteria','| Criterion | MYP Arts name | Plain-language meaning | What it asks students to do |
|-----------|---------------|------------------------|-----------------------------|
| **A** | Investigating (Knowing & understanding) | Research and understand | Investigate a movement/genre/artist; analyse artworks; use subject-specific vocabulary; connect context to the statement of inquiry |
| **B** | Developing | Plan and experiment | Practically explore techniques and ideas; develop and communicate a clear **artistic intention**; make and record informed choices |
| **C** | Creating (Performing) | Make the artwork | Create/realise a finished artwork that applies skills and techniques and fulfils the artistic intention |
| **D** | Evaluating | Judge and reflect | Appraise the finished artwork against the intention; reflect on personal artistic development and the creative process |

> Each criterion is marked out of **8** (levels 1–8) using MYP task-specific clarifications of the published rubric strands.','{"the":8,"four":1,"myp":3,"arts":2,"criteria":1,"criterion":2,"name":1,"plain":1,"language":1,"meaning":1,"what":1,"asks":1,"students":1,"investigating":1,"knowing":1,"understanding":1,"research":1,"and":9,"understand":1,"investigate":1,"movement":1,"genre":1,"artist":1,"analyse":1,"artworks":1,"use":1,"subject":1,"specific":2,"vocabulary":1,"connect":1,"context":1,"statement":1,"inquiry":1,"developing":1,"plan":1,"experiment":1,"practically":1,"explore":1,"techniques":2,"ideas":1,"develop":1,"communicate":1,"clear":1,"artistic":3,"intention":3,"make":2,"record":1,"informed":1,"choices":1,"creating":1,"performing":1,"artwork":3,"create":1,"realise":1,"finished":2,"that":1,"applies":1,"skills":1,"fulfils":1,"evaluating":1,"judge":1,"reflect":2,"appraise":1,"against":1,"personal":1,"development":1,"creative":1,"process":1,"each":1,"marked":1,"out":1,"levels":1,"using":1,"task":1,"clarifications":1,"published":1,"rubric":1,"strands":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_a2038678941ade0bf3','file_1dcbc968a2bb8c1157','visual-art.md','Arts Related Concepts (used across the year)','**Composition, Expression, Interpretation, Style, Genre, Visual culture, Representation, Innovation, Boundaries, Audience, Narrative, Presentation.**

Quick definitions:
- **Composition** — how the parts of an artwork are arranged within the frame.
- **Expression** — communicating feeling, mood or idea through visual choices.
- **Interpretation** — the meaning a viewer or artist reads into/from an artwork.
- **Style** — the recognisable, consistent visual "signature" of an artist or movement.
- **Genre** — a category/type of art (e.g., landscape, portrait, still life).
- **Visual culture** — the images and visual practices of a society.
- **Representation** — how something real or imagined is depicted.
- **Innovation** — new ideas, methods or ways of seeing.
- **Boundaries** — the limits (of media, convention, tradition) an artist works within or breaks.
- **Audience** — the viewers an artwork is made for or received by.
- **Narrative** — the story or sequence an artwork communicates.
- **Presentation** — how finished work is displayed and shared.

