('chunk_df96b2fe525162f716','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','1.1 The MYP Language Acquisition Group','Spanish, French and Hindi at Grade 7 sit in the **IB MYP Language Acquisition** subject group. The purpose of Language Acquisition is to enable students to develop the ability to communicate in a target language (an additional language beyond the language of instruction/mother tongue) and to gain insight into and respect for other cultures and world views. Learning is organised into **six phases** (Emergent phases 1–2, Capable phases 3–4, Proficient phases 5–6). Grade 7 learners at IISH work primarily in the **Emergent phase (phases 1–2)**.

**What "Emergent" means.** Emergent-phase students are early language learners. They:
- comprehend and respond to simple, familiar spoken, written and visual texts;
- interact in basic, rehearsed exchanges about everyday topics (self, family, school, routine);
- produce short, simple texts using a limited but growing range of vocabulary, high-frequency structures and memorised chunks;
- rely on visual support, cognates, gestures and context to construct meaning;
- make frequent errors that do not usually prevent basic communication.
Teaching therefore prioritises **high-frequency vocabulary, present tense, simple sentence patterns, modelled text types, and heavy scaffolding** (word banks, sentence starters, visuals, bilingual glossaries).','{"the":6,"myp":2,"language":7,"acquisition":3,"group":2,"spanish":1,"french":1,"and":9,"hindi":1,"grade":2,"sit":1,"subject":1,"purpose":1,"enable":1,"students":2,"develop":1,"ability":1,"communicate":1,"target":1,"additional":1,"beyond":1,"instruction":1,"mother":1,"tongue":1,"gain":1,"insight":1,"into":2,"respect":1,"for":1,"other":1,"cultures":1,"world":1,"views":1,"learning":1,"organised":1,"six":1,"phases":5,"emergent":4,"capable":1,"proficient":1,"learners":2,"iish":1,"work":1,"primarily":1,"phase":2,"what":1,"means":1,"are":1,"early":1,"they":1,"comprehend":1,"respond":1,"simple":3,"familiar":1,"spoken":1,"written":1,"visual":2,"texts":2,"interact":1,"basic":2,"rehearsed":1,"exchanges":1,"about":1,"everyday":1,"topics":1,"self":1,"family":1,"school":1,"routine":1,"produce":1,"short":1,"using":1,"limited":1,"but":1,"growing":1,"range":1,"vocabulary":2,"high":2,"frequency":2,"structures":1,"memorised":1,"chunks":1,"rely":1,"support":1,"cognates":1,"gestures":1,"context":1,"construct":1,"meaning":1,"make":1,"frequent":1,"errors":1,"that":1,"not":1,"usually":1,"prevent":1,"communication":1,"teaching":1,"therefore":1,"prioritises":1,"present":1,"tense":1,"sentence":2,"patterns":1,"modelled":1,"text":1,"types":1,"heavy":1,"scaffolding":1,"word":1,"banks":1,"starters":1,"visuals":1,"bilingual":1,"glossaries":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_0319a0df8fd10f607e','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','1.2 The Four MYP Language Acquisition Criteria','All three Emergent languages are assessed against the same four criteria, each out of **8 marks** (band descriptors 1–2, 3–4, 5–6, 7–8):

| Criterion | Title | What it assesses |
|-----------|-------|------------------|
| **A** | Comprehending spoken and visual text | Listening: understanding spoken and audio-visual texts, identifying information, drawing conclusions, recognising conventions. |
| **B** | Comprehending written and visual text | Reading: understanding written and visual texts, identifying information, interpreting, recognising conventions. |
| **C** | Communicating in response to spoken, written and visual text | Speaking/interaction: responding, communicating information and ideas, interacting, using phases-appropriate language. |
| **D** | Using language in spoken and written form | Producing: writing and speaking accurately, organising information, using vocabulary/grammar/conventions appropriate to the phase. |

> **Note on labels.** Some teachers shorthand these as A = Listening, B = Reading, C = Speaking, D = Writing. The official focus is comprehension (A, B) and production/interaction (C, D). Criterion C is interactive/communicative; D is about accuracy and range of language use.','{"the":4,"four":2,"myp":1,"language":4,"acquisition":1,"criteria":2,"all":1,"three":1,"emergent":1,"languages":1,"are":1,"assessed":1,"against":1,"same":1,"each":1,"out":1,"marks":1,"band":1,"descriptors":1,"criterion":2,"title":1,"what":1,"assesses":1,"comprehending":2,"spoken":4,"and":10,"visual":5,"text":3,"listening":2,"understanding":2,"audio":1,"texts":2,"identifying":2,"information":4,"drawing":1,"conclusions":1,"recognising":2,"conventions":3,"written":4,"reading":2,"interpreting":1,"communicating":2,"response":1,"speaking":3,"interaction":2,"responding":1,"ideas":1,"interacting":1,"using":3,"phases":1,"appropriate":2,"form":1,"producing":1,"writing":2,"accurately":1,"organising":1,"vocabulary":1,"grammar":1,"phase":1,"note":1,"labels":1,"some":1,"teachers":1,"shorthand":1,"these":1,"official":1,"focus":1,"comprehension":1,"production":1,"interactive":1,"communicative":1,"about":1,"accuracy":1,"range":1,"use":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_4885d18167576d41c9','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','1.3 Telugu — a Language & Literature-style frame','Telugu at IISH is taught as a **mother-tongue / Language & Literature-style** course (based on **"Telugu Vennela 2"**), not as an acquisition course. Rather than the four Acquisition criteria, it is framed around the MYP **Language & Literature** competencies — analysing, organising, producing text, and using language — delivered through prose, poetry and value-based lessons. Its emphasis is reading comprehension, vocabulary enrichment, grammar, and speaking/writing for students who already speak Telugu at home. It is detailed in Section 5.','{"telugu":4,"language":4,"literature":3,"style":2,"frame":1,"iish":1,"taught":1,"mother":1,"tongue":1,"course":2,"based":2,"vennela":1,"not":1,"acquisition":2,"rather":1,"than":1,"the":2,"four":1,"criteria":1,"framed":1,"around":1,"myp":1,"competencies":1,"analysing":1,"organising":1,"producing":1,"text":1,"and":3,"using":1,"delivered":1,"through":1,"prose":1,"poetry":1,"value":1,"lessons":1,"its":1,"emphasis":1,"reading":1,"comprehension":1,"vocabulary":1,"enrichment":1,"grammar":1,"speaking":1,"writing":1,"for":1,"students":1,"who":1,"already":1,"speak":1,"home":1,"detailed":1,"section":1}'::jsonb),
('chunk_43410da51289093768','file_c827a0b7bfd97ec469','world-languages.md','1.4 Related Concepts for Language Acquisition','These recur across all units and languages and should be woven into inquiry:
**audience, context, conventions, form, function, meaning, message, purpose, word choice, structure** (and, in Acquisition, also *idiom, patterns, point of view*).

